            <ol class="comment-threads">
                                <li id="comment-thread-27847635" class="comment-thread">
        <div class="comment  " id="comment-27847635">
        <p class="comment-user-logo">
            <img class="userLogo logo anonymous" src="../../s/en_GB/5982/f2b47fb3d636c8bc9fd0b11c0ec6d0ae18646be7.1/_/images/icons/profilepics/anonymous.png"
           alt="User icon: cwsteinbach" title="cwsteinbach">        </p>
        <div class="comment-header">
            <h4 class="author">    <a href="https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/~cwsteinbach"
                       class="url fn"
                            >Carl Steinbach</a></h4>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-body">
            <div class="comment-content wiki-content">
                <blockquote><p>What extensions to the authorization system are you thinking of?</p></blockquote>

<p>Add a new privilege named something like &quot;select_cross_db&quot; and GRANT it to specific users as follows:</p>

<p>GRANT select_cross_db ON DATABASE db TO USER x;<br />
GRANT select_cross_db ON DATABASE db to ROLE x;</p>

<p>This privilege would be provided by default, but if absent, then the user would be prevented from referencing DBs outside of 'db' while using 'db' as the primary database.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="comment-actions">
                                                <ul class="comment-actions-secondary">
                                                              <li class="first comment-permalink"><a title="Permanent link to this comment" href="Links@focusedCommentId=27847635#comment-27847635"
